race.comment: BLUEPINOT (1) led in a new role for him last start at Geelong and he responded by registering a second career win. Steps up 150m in trip which is to his advantage. Won't find this any tougher so he presents as a winning chance again. SARRISMO (2) made it five podium finishes from as many career runs when runner-up after leading over 1625m at Wyong last time out. Not drawn the best but if he slots in with cover he poses a serious threat. AUTOMNE TREE (3) started favourite but after copping some interference at the beginning of the run home he missed the placings last Wednesday over 1500m at Rosehill. Fitter for two runs back from a spell and he won his only race over this course and distance when third-up. BIG TIGER (4) backs up seven days after a tough all-the-way maiden win over 1400m at Rosehill. Has only raced twice so there is plenty of upside to this Waterhouse/Bott colt. Last start Warwick Farm maiden winner SWIFT LEGEND (6) keeps improving and isn't out of place here.
